Title: Non-abelian gauge theories as a consequence of perturbative quantum
  gauge invariance
Authors: Andreas Aste, G"unter Scharf
Comments: 12 pages, latex, no figures
Report-no: ZU-TH-6/98
Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A14 (1999) 3421-3434
\\
  We show for the case of interacting massless vector bosons, how the structure
of Yang-Mills theories emerges automatically from a more fundamental concept,
namely perturbative quantum gauge invariance. It turns out that the coupling in
a non-abelian gauge theory is necessarily of Yang-Mills type plus divergence-
and coboundary couplings. The extension of the method to massive gauge theories
is briefly discussed.
